Kamal Haasan is an Indian actor, screenwriter and director considered one of the leading method actors of Indian cinema. He has won numerous awards including 4 National Film Awards and many Filmfare Awards. He is known for acting in the largest number of films submitted by India for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film. After starting as a child artist, he had his breakthrough role in 1975's Apoorva Raagangal. Some of his notable films include Nayagan (1987), for which he won his third National Award, and Dasavathaaram in which he played 10 roles. He has also produced several of his own films through his production company Rajkamal International.
